President Trump and Prime Minister Abe of Japan held a press conference during the G7 summit in France. They discussed their strong relationship and ongoing discussions on trade, military cooperation, and North Korea. President Trump also expressed support for Prime Minister Abe's outreach to Iran. The leaders mentioned the possibility of inviting Russia back to the G7, but no decision was made. They also addressed North Korea's recent missile tests, with President Trump expressing confidence that Kim Jong Un will do the right thing in the end.